Types of Threat Intelligence:

1. Strategic
  - High level analysis: trends, risks, impacts
  - Threat actor motives, goals, and capabilities
  - Deciding long-term security strategy
2. Tactical
  - Tactics, techniques, and procedures (TTPs)
  - Threat actor behavior and methodologies
3. Operational
  - Imminent threats, plans, and timelines
  - Tracking threat actors and groups
4. Technical
  - Tools, infrastructure, and technical capabilities
  - Indicators of Compromise (IOCs)
  - Integrate into tooling to enhance detection methods

Resources:
https://www.mandiant.com/sites/default/files/2021-09/APT28-Center-of-Storm-2017.pdf
https://attack.mitre.org/

Intelligence Cycle:
1. Requirements and Direction (Planning)
2. Collection (Processing)
3. Analysis
4. Dissemination
5. Feedback

OSINT:
- Dark web, forums, social media
- Passive recon, vulnerability, and malware databases
- Public repositories
Comercial Threat Intelligence:
- Third-party vendors
- Proprietary subscription-based threat feeds
- IOCs, malware signatures, attack patterns
Vendor Reports and Security Research:
- Published reports and whitepapers
ISACs Centers:
 - Auto - ISAC
 - Aviation ISAC
 - Water ISAC
 - Electricity: E-ISAC
 - Space ISAC


Diamond Model of Intrusion Analysis
!(https://www.socinvestigation.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/09/FIN8.png)
- Adversary ( who are they? what country? motivation? ideology? etc)
- Capability
- Infrastructure (physical servers, endpoints, malicious domains, etc)
- Victim (connects to the attack


